Package-Data-Inheritable version 0.05

DESCRIPTION

A pure perl module to provide inheritable and overridable package variables
without the need for accessor methods. After declaration, the variables can be
used like ordinary package variables. Scalars can be declared constant.
Internally the module relies on Exporter to propagate variables down the
inheritance hierarchy.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc Package::Data::Inheritable

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Package-Data-Inheritable

    CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Package-Data-Inheritable

    AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Package-Data-Inheritable

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Package-Data-Inheritable

